data.title: Jamie Lynn Spears reveals wedding ring next to husband Jamie Watson
data.meta_description: Jamie Lynn Spears made her first red carpet appearance since becoming a married woman, showing off her wedding ring
data.text:
Jamie Lynn Spears has made her first red carpet appearance since becoming a married woman.

The 23-year-old singer rocked up to the Academy Of Country Music Awards in Las Vegas, accompanied by her doting husband Jamie Watson.

Jamie Lynn looked like she was on cloud nine as she walked up the carpet in a geometric pattern, sequined dress. The blonde bombshell showed off her petite frame and toned legs in the figure-hugging number and completed her look with neon red heels.

Jamie Lynn Spears at the Academy Of Country Music Awards

All attention was focused on Jamie Lynn's latest accessory though â€” her beautiful wedding ring. The thick silver band sat alongside her monster engagement diamond rock which sparkled as she posed for photographs.

Fans of the Mississippi-born star first saw Jamie Lynn's engagement ring when she posted a photo on Twitter of her and Jamie announcing their happy news. "Guess what?" she captioned it, followed by another close-up snap of the impressive round-cut jewel.

Jamie Lynn's show-stopping wedding cake: get all the details here

Jamie Lynn left all attention to her wedding and engagement rings

At Sunday's event in Sin City, it was a mix of business and pleasure for Jamie Lynn as she took on the role of social media correspondent for the awards. The night seems to have been successful as she thanked her country musician Kellie Pickler on the night.

"Thank you @KelliePickler for being so sweet and guiding me thru my first #ACMs!" she tweeted, next to a photo of the pair.

Jamie Lynn's wedding photos revealed

Jamie Lynn and Jamie tied the knot last month

Speaking on the red carpet, Jamie Lynn also opened up about her debut song How Could I Want More and her pop icon sister Britney Spears.

"I worked on this project for a really long time," she said. "The single means a lot to me, and I was finally brave enough to put it out there." Your sister is always someone you're going to look up to. We're in the same kind of industry but different genres, so definitely it's good to take her advice."
